CRITICAL SAFETY WARNING — PLEASE READ BEFORE USE

This skill gives an AI agent (Claude or any skill-aware assistant) the
ability to read, send, edit, delete, and react to messages on your
behalf in any Slack workspace whose User OAuth Token you grant it. The
agent acts AS YOU — every API call carries your identity. There is NO
sandboxing and NO per-call confirmation; the only safeguards are
instructions in the skill telling the agent to confirm sensitive
actions before performing them, which is enforcement by convention,
not by mechanism.

Potential consequences of misuse include but are not limited to:
- Sending unintended messages to colleagues, channels, or DMs under
  your name and identity
- Posting confidential, sensitive, or embarrassing content to the
  wrong audience
- Permanent deletion or irreversible editing of messages
- Adding or removing reactions on messages, visible to all members
- Marking channels or DMs as read, hiding genuinely unread items
- Reading and exfiltrating private channel history, DMs, and search
  results that the agent then summarizes, stores, or forwards
- Triggering notifications, mentions, and broadcasts to large groups
- Violating workplace acceptable-use policies, NDAs, or applicable
  law through agent-driven actions taken in your name

Risks specific to AI-driven use:
- An agent may misinterpret a request and send the wrong message to
  the wrong channel, person, or workspace
- A prompt-injection payload reaching the agent — embedded in message
  content, search results, channel topics, file contents, or pasted
  material — could direct it to send, delete, or exfiltrate messages
- A hallucinated channel name, user ID, or timestamp may produce
  unintended writes to a different conversation
- The agent acting under your User OAuth Token cannot be distinguished
  by Slack or your colleagues from actions you took yourself
- Audit logs (where available) attribute the action to YOU, not to
  the agent

Recovery expectations:
- Slack message editing and deletion is auditable to administrators
  but not silently reversible — recipients see edit and delete
  indicators, and may have already read or quoted the original
- Workspace retention settings determine whether deleted messages
  remain recoverable by administrators; the skill itself maintains no
  backups
- Reactions, read state, and pin/star/bookmark changes have no undo
  beyond manually reversing them

